2. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The model is evaluated on text classification and language modeling tasks. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new neural network architecture for improving performance on sequential tasks. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses recurrent neural networks as the basis for the proposed Thick-Net model. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The model is also evaluated on the permuted sequential MNIST task, which involves image sequences.
